        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 17 at 3:58PM CDT until September 17 at 4:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 21 miles southwest
of Wolf Creek Park, or 22 miles southeast of Spearman, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. Hail damage to vehicles is
expected.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northern Roberts and southwestern Ochiltree Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
